## Standard Operating Procedure — Multi-Agent Analysis & Feedback Engine

**Version:** 1.0  
**Effective Date:** 2026-05-15  
**Owner:** InsightProfit Engineering  
**Status:** Active  

---

## 1. Purpose

This SOP defines the operational procedures for the Agentic Intelligence Platform — an interactive web application that accepts user inputs (URLs, text, images, video) and delivers professional-grade AI analysis through specialized agent personas. The initial deployment covers the CRO (Conversion Rate Optimization) agent, with a scalable architecture supporting all C-suite agent roles (CMO, CFO, CTO, COO, etc.).

---

## 2. Scope

- **Phase 1 (Current):** CRO Agent — website/landing page analysis, conversion audit, UX friction detection, improvement recommendations with predicted ROI
- **Phase 2:** CMO Agent — marketing strategy analysis, brand positioning, campaign audit
- **Phase 3:** Full C-Suite expansion — CFO (financial analysis), CTO (tech stack audit), COO (operations optimization), CHRO (workforce analysis), CSO (sales strategy)
- **Future:** Custom agent creation from job descriptions in the Job Tracker Sheet

---

## 3. System Architecture

### 3.1 Components

| Component | Role | Location |
|-----------|------|----------|
| Frontend App | User interface, input collection, report display | Viktor Space (Vercel) |
| Convex Backend | Real-time database, analysis queue, report storage | Convex cloud |
| Viktor Tool Gateway | AI analysis engine (web scraping, image analysis, LLM reasoning) | Viktor SDK |
| Hermes Orchestrator | Multi-agent coordination, task routing, workflow management | hermes.insightprofit.live |
| Agent Registry | Agent persona definitions, prompt templates, scoring rubrics | Convex tables |

### 3.2 Data Flow

```
User Input → Frontend → Convex Mutation → Analysis Queue
    → Viktor Tool Gateway (scrape/analyze) 
    → Hermes Orchestration (multi-agent coordination)
    → Structured Report Generation
    → Convex Storage → Frontend Display
```

### 3.3 Input Types

| Input Type | Processing Method | Use Case |
|-----------|-------------------|----------|
| URL | Browser scraping + screenshot + Lighthouse + content extraction | Website/page CRO audit |
| Text | Direct LLM analysis | Copy review, strategy docs, job descriptions |
| Image (drag & drop) | Vision model analysis | Ad creative review, landing page screenshots |
| Video/File Upload | File-to-markdown + frame extraction | Video ad review, presentation audit |

---

## 4. Agent Persona Framework

### 4.1 CRO Agent (Phase 1)

**Role:** Chief Revenue Optimizer  
**Expertise:** Conversion rate optimization, UX analysis, landing page auditing, funnel optimization, A/B testing strategy

**Analysis Modules:**
1. **Page Performance Scan** — Load speed, Core Web Vitals, mobile responsiveness
2. **Above-the-Fold Audit** — Headline clarity, value proposition, CTA visibility
3. **Trust & Social Proof** — Testimonials, logos, security badges, guarantees
4. **User Flow Analysis** — Navigation friction, form complexity, checkout flow
5. **Copy & Messaging** — Headline formulas, benefit-driven language, urgency/scarcity
6. **Visual Hierarchy** — Layout, whitespace, contrast, visual flow
7. **Competitive Positioning** — Differentiation, pricing presentation, objection handling

**Output Structure:**
```
├── Executive Summary (score + 1-paragraph verdict)
├── What's Working (3-7 strengths with evidence)
├── What's Not Working (3-7 issues ranked by impact)
├── Specific Recommendations (5-10 actionable items)
│   ├── Priority (Critical / High / Medium / Low)
│   ├── Current State (what exists now)
│   ├── Recommended Change (specific action)
│   ├── Expected Impact (% improvement estimate)
│   └── Implementation Effort (hours/complexity)
├── Predicted Impact Summary
│   ├── Estimated Conversion Lift (%)
│   ├── Estimated Revenue Impact ($/period)
│   └── Confidence Level (High/Medium/Low)
└── Implementation Plan
    ├── Quick Wins (< 1 day)
    ├── Short-term (1-2 weeks)
    └── Strategic (1-3 months)
```

### 4.2 Scaling to New Agents

Each new agent requires:
1. **Persona Definition** — Role, expertise areas, analysis scope
2. **Prompt Template** — System prompt with domain expertise injection
3. **Scoring Rubric** — Weighted criteria for the agent's domain
4. **Output Template** — Structured sections for that agent type
5. **Input Preprocessing** — Domain-specific data extraction logic

**Agent Addition Checklist:**
- [ ] Create agent persona in Agent Registry (Convex)
- [ ] Write system prompt with domain expertise
- [ ] Define scoring rubric (weighted criteria)
- [ ] Create output template sections
- [ ] Add agent card to frontend selection UI
- [ ] Test with 5+ sample inputs
- [ ] Deploy and monitor first 50 analyses

---

## 5. Operational Procedures

### 5.1 Analysis Request Flow

1. User selects agent persona (e.g., CRO Agent)
2. User provides input (URL, text, image, or file upload)
3. System validates input and creates analysis record in Convex
4. Backend triggers Viktor Tool Gateway:
   - URL → scrape page content, take screenshot, extract metadata
   - Text → tokenize and prepare for analysis
   - Image → upload to storage, prepare for vision analysis
   - Video → extract frames, transcribe audio
5. Hermes orchestrates multi-step analysis pipeline
6. AI generates structured report using agent persona prompt
7. Report stored in Convex, displayed in real-time to user
8. User can export report (PDF) or share via link

### 5.2 Quality Assurance

- Every analysis includes a confidence score (0-100)
- Low-confidence sections flagged with disclaimers
- Reports include evidence citations (screenshots, data points)
- Users can provide feedback (thumbs up/down) on recommendations
- Feedback loop improves future analyses

### 5.3 Rate Limiting & Cost Management

| Tier | Analyses/Day | Max Input Size | Token Budget |
|------|-------------|----------------|--------------|
| Free | 3 | 10 pages | 50K tokens |
| Pro | 25 | 50 pages | 500K tokens |
| Enterprise | Unlimited | Unlimited | Custom |

---

## 6. Hermes Integration

### 6.1 Orchestration Pattern

Hermes serves as the multi-agent coordinator:

```yaml
workflow: cro_analysis
steps:
  - agent: data_collector
    action: scrape_and_screenshot
    input: user_url
    
  - agent: performance_analyst
    action: lighthouse_audit
    input: user_url
    
  - agent: ux_expert
    action: analyze_layout_and_flow
    input: [screenshot, page_content]
    
  - agent: copy_strategist
    action: evaluate_messaging
    input: page_content
    
  - agent: cro_synthesizer
    action: compile_report
    input: [all_previous_outputs]
    output: structured_report
```

### 6.2 API Endpoints (hermes.insightprofit.live)

- `POST /api/analyze` — Submit analysis request
- `GET /api/status/{task_id}` — Check analysis progress
- `GET /api/report/{task_id}` — Retrieve completed report
- `POST /api/agents` — Register new agent persona

---

## 7. Security & Privacy

- User-submitted URLs are accessed read-only (no login, no form submission)
- Uploaded files are stored temporarily (24hr TTL) then deleted
- No PII extraction from analyzed pages
- All analysis requests logged with user ID for audit trail
- HTTPS everywhere, Convex auth for user sessions

---

## 8. Monitoring & Metrics

| Metric | Target | Alert Threshold |
|--------|--------|----------------|
| Analysis completion time | < 60 seconds | > 120 seconds |
| Success rate | > 95% | < 90% |
| User satisfaction (feedback) | > 80% positive | < 70% |
| Token cost per analysis | < $0.15 | > $0.30 |
| Daily active analyses | Growing | 0 for 3+ days |

